# Prompt.md — StudySphere | AI-Powered Study Tracker

Build a futuristic and responsive full-stack Study Tracker web application called “StudySphere” using Flask, SQLite, HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, and Chart.js.

The UI should have:
- Dark futuristic glassmorphism design
- Neon gradients
- Smooth hover animations
- Interactive dashboard cards
- Responsive mobile-first layout

Core Features:
1. User Authentication
- Register/Login/Logout
- Secure password hashing
- Session management

2. Study Session Tracking
- Add study sessions
- Subject name
- Duration in hours/minutes
- Notes
- Date selection

3. Subject Categories
Include:
- Mathematics
- Programming
- Science
- AI & Machine Learning
- Data Structures
- Web Development
- Aptitude
- Other

4. Analytics Dashboard
Display:
- Total study hours
- Weekly study analytics
- Subject-wise breakdown
- Productivity trends
- Daily streak tracker
- Completion percentage

5. Pomodoro Timer
- 25/5 study timer
- Start/Pause/Reset buttons
- Animated circular progress

6. Goal Management
- Daily goals
- Weekly targets
- Completion tracker
- Progress bars

7. Charts
Use Chart.js for:
- Weekly study chart
- Subject distribution chart
- Monthly productivity graph

8. Notes & Revision
- Save quick notes
- Mark revision completed
- Highlight important topics

9. Export Features
- Export study data as CSV
- Download study reports

10. Settings Page
- Theme settings
- User profile
- Reset data
- Reminder preferences

Tech Stack:
Backend:
- Flask
- Flask-SQLAlchemy
- Flask-Login
- Flask-Bcrypt

Frontend:
- Bootstrap 5
- HTML5
- CSS3
- JavaScript
- Chart.js

Database:
- SQLite

Pages Required:
